  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Given the tendency of keywordbased automated assessments to overinflate ASRs, we implement strict manual evaluation on both the Advbench's [30] harmful behaviors and the VAJM [20] evaluation set.",
    "Attacks that generate relevant and useful harmful output are defined as successful, with others considered failures.",
    "Toxicity Rate.",
    "To measure the toxicity of continuations generated on the RealToxicityPrompts benchmark [10], we utilize the Perspective API and the Detoxify classifier [13], both of which can calculate toxicity scores for a set of six toxic attributes.",
    "Scores range from 0 (least toxic) to 1 (most toxic)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
